  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375F (190C).",
    "In a saucepan, melt the butter and sauté the minced garlic until translucent, about 1 minute.",
    "Add the heavy cream and bring to a gentle simmer, then stir in the grated Gruyere until smooth.",
    "Season the mixture with fresh thyme, nutmeg, salt, pepper, and the infused olive oil, stirring until fully combined.",
    "Pour the sauce into a small baking dish, spreading it evenly.",
    "Sprinkle the almond flour evenly over the top.",
    "Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, or until the surface is golden brown and the cheese is bubbly.",
    "Remove from the oven and let the gratin rest for 5 minutes.",
    "Garnish with chopped parsley and serve hot."
  ],
